author: Peter Devlin For Daily Mail Australia
title: New Zealand couple didn't know they had won $18million | Daily Mail Online
text: comments A young New Zealand couple who thought they'd pocketed $18,000 on lotto were surprised to find they'd actually won $18 million. The pair, who are expecting their first child, received an email on Sunday saying they had won Lotto, Stuff reported. 'So I logged into MyLotto account and saw the prize and thought, "Oh yeah, cool,"' the man, who wished to remain anonymous, said. A young New Zealand couple who thought they'd pocketed $18,000 on lotto were surprised to find they'd actually won $18 million (stock image) He didn't realise just how much they'd won until he filled out the prize form and showed his wife. 'A bunch of our friends and family were around and I was pretty chuffed so I strolled into the lounge and told everyone we'd just won $18,000 with Lotto,' he said. RELATED ARTICLES
